docs.lead_paragraph: Babies who are allowed to linger in the womb are often healthier and do better in school.

headline.main: Heavier Babies Do Better in School

docs.abstract: The Upshot; study to be published in American Economic Review calls into question some of the most basic assumptions of a medicalized approach to childbirth; data suggests that many fetuses might benefit by staying longer in the womb.
docs.snippet: Babies who are allowed to linger in the womb are often healthier and do better in school.

byline.original: By DAVID LEONHARDT and AMANDA COX

docs.lead_paragraph: President Barack Obama is targeting his midterm election economic message to young people born after 1980, a cohort that has shown itself to be reluctant to vote in nonpresidential contests.

headline.main: Obama to Target Millennials With Economic Pitch
headline.print_headline: Obama to Target Millennials With Economic Pitch
